He very politely pointed out a seat to her.
What can I do for you?
She could hardly get out her words, but at last she managed to say: I have come for this.
The manager looked at the object that she held out to him in mute astonishment.
It looks to me to be in a very bad state of health, he said compassionately.
It cost me twenty francs, she said, with some hesitation.
He seemed astonished.
As much as that?
But I really dont understand what it has to do with me.
She began to feel uncomfortable; perhaps this company did not pay for such small articles, and she said:
Butwits burned.
He could not deny it.
I see that very well, he replied.
She felt her courage reviving.
She was not going to give up without a struggle.
She was not even afraid any more, and said:
Im Madame Oreille; were insured by your company, and Ive come to claim the value of this damage.
I only want you to pay me the cost of re-covering it.
The gentleman seemed rather confused.
Really, its such a very small matter!
Were never asked to give compensation for such trivial losses.
She got red in the face, and felt inclined to fly into a rage.
Your company is supposed to compensate for ANYTHING burned in my house!
As he thought that he had no chance of getting rid of her, and that he would only be wasting his time, he said resignedly, What do you estimate the damage at?
Well, I dont want to make any money out of you, so Ill tell you what well do.
Ill take my umbrella to the maker, who will re-cover it, and Ill bring the bill to you.
Will that suit you?
Perfectly, well settle it so.
Here is a note for the cashier, who will repay you whatever it costs you.
He gave Madame Oreille a slip of paper; she took it, got up and went out, thanking him, for she was in a hurry to escape lest he should change his mind.
She went briskly through the streets, looking out for a really good umbrella maker, and when she found a shop, which appeared to be a first-class one, she went in, and said, confidently:
I want this umbrella re-covered in silk, good silk.
Use the very best and strongest you have.
I dont mind what it costs.
